HEADWORD: Detonation
<hw>Det`o*na"tion</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧t`⟦osl⟧*n⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧tonation</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
explosion or sudden report made by the instantaneous decomposition or
combustion of unstable substances; <as>as, the <ex>detonation</ex> of
gun cotton</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Detonator</ent>⟦br⟧
